	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Sun, Jan 26th 11:27 AM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=181619><span id= >animekenji</span></a><br><span id=notbold>378 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.83]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>They should bring these things back. They had a legitimate use. Tailoring items requiring more than 8 ingredients when you are far away from a loom. I don't see how these could possibly kill the tailored bag market, since there is no weight reduction. I would have preferred to see VI give tailored bags a bigger weight reduction and lower the amount that the bags themselves actually weigh, rather than take an amazingly useful item such as this out of game permanently.<br><br>When they made rockhopper hides usable in place of HQ bear skins and made them a lot easier to get than HQ bear skins, nobody complained. This encouraged people to take up tailoring to make their own bags for fun and profit and flooded the game with bags and people with the ability to make them. Has that hurt prices?? Not much by what I have seen. What makes you think the Deluxe Sewing Kit would have hurt the bag market?<br><br>And why hasn't anyone bitched about the Deluxe Toolbox in the same way that they bitched about this? It also holds 10 GIANT sized items and weighs .5 LESS than the Deluxe Sewing Kit!! You people should be in a bigger uproar over those than the sewing kits. <br><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Sun Jan 26 11:08:11 2003</em></p>&nbsp;<br>If you were me and I were you, would we still be friends?</td></td></tr>
